JSP Tags

JSP scripting language include several tags or scripting elements that performs various tasks such as 
declaring variables and methods, writing expressions, and calling other JSP pages. 
These are known as JSP scripting elements. 
The different types of scripting elements are summarized as:


1. Directive Tag

Specifies translation time instructions to the JSP engine.

<%@ directives %>

2. Declaration Tag

Declaration Declares and defines methods and variables.

<%! variable dceclaration & method definition %>

3. Scriptlet Tag

Allows the developer to write free-form Java code in a JSP page.

<% some Java code %>

4. Expression Tag

Used as a shortcut to print values in the output HTML of a JSP page.

<%= an Expression %>

5. Action Tag

Provides request-time instructions to the JSP engine.

<jsp:actionName />
 
6. Comment Tag

Used for documentation and for commenting out parts of JSP code.

<%– any Text –%>


Example code showing different types of JSP Tags:

<%-- Counter.jsp --%>             <%-- Comment Tag --%>

<%@ page language="java" %>       <%-- Directive Tag --%>
<%! int count = 0; %>             <%-- Declaration Tag --%>
<% count++; %>                    <%-- Scriptlet Tag --%>
Welcome! You are visitor number
<%= count %>                      <%-- Expression Tag --%>


For more details about JSP Tags, visit https://www.techguruspeaks.com/jsp-tags/
